/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Real-message samples never committed to public repo (see docs/sample-policy.md, Phase 0 S2).
# Use /samples/* (not /samples/) so git still recurses INTO the dir — a whole-dir
# exclusion blocks recursion, which silently disables samples/.gitignore and even the
# .gitkeep negations below. samples/.gitignore governs the per-subdir rules: it keeps
# samples/iso8583/ as the (empty) real-sample slot and re-includes the committed,
# clearly-labelled samples/synthetic/ demo subtree.
/samples/*
*.hex
*.bin
*.swift
!samples/.gitkeep

# Raw, unsanitized acquisition candidates — held local-only until sanitizer
# round-trip-verifies them and promotes the redacted form into samples/.
# See docs/sample-policy.md and tools/sample-sanitize/README.md.
/candidates/

# Standalone tool crates that are NOT workspace members keep their own target/.
/tools/sample-sanitize/target/

# Built MCP bundles — shipped as GitHub Release assets, never committed.
/mcpb/dist/
